@server = http://localhost:8081
### SIGN UP user (creates entry in users collection)
POST http://localhost:8081/user/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}
###

### GET profile BEFORE it exists (profile will be null)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/UserProfile/testuser
###

### UPDATE profile (creates profile if missing)
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/UserProfile/testuser
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bio": "My profile",
  "avatarUrl": "https://site.com/avatar.png",
  "coins": 100
}
###

### GET profile AFTER update (profile should now exist)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/UserProfile/testuser
###

### GET profile for user that does NOT exist (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/UserProfile/notARealUser
###

### UPDATE profile with only one field (bio)
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/UserProfile/testuser
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "bio": "Bio"
}
###

### GET again to confirm bio updated
GET http://localhost:8081/api/UserProfile/testuser

### Delete Profile
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/UserProfile/account/testuser

